originalText.text: We had an incredible experience with Jenna McKay when buying our apartment in Brooklyn Heights. We were first time homebuyers in New York City and she helped us through a lengthy search and closing process. We were lucky to have Jenna in our corner as we navigated the negotiation process and couldn't be happier with our new home. She was responsive, had deep relationships, and we probably wouldn't have ended up getting this unit without her expertise. 10/10 would work with Jenna as our realtor again.

originalText.text:
Working with Jenna was an absolute dream. She was available to help us in every step of this process. As first time home buyers, we were quite picky about neighborhood, budget, school districts, and apartment style. Jenna checked out apartments with my wife and I everywhere from the West Village to Park Slope. When we finally found the Cobble Hill spot that we thought could be "the one," Jenna was able to put in an offer on our behalf on the same day. More than one offer had been made on the apartment, and Jenna was able to negotiate a deal for us, still coming in under asking price! She is incredibly detail-oriented, and was able to guide us through the process with clarity and ease. There is so much we would have missed if we would not have had Jenna navigating the deal for us. She also set us up with a team to take care of the mortgage, inspection, and legal aspect of purchasing property. Everyone recommended by Jenna was professional, thorough, and efficient, in addition to being friendly and easy to work with.
Our expected closing date landed right at the start of the Stay At Home order here in NYC, so we were very worried about the closing. Turns out, we were in great hands. Jenna and her team made sure we were able to safely do a final walk through, sign closing papers, and even have a socially distant notary come to our apartment lobby to witness the signing. None of that would have been possible without Jenna.
It would be impossible to put into words how grateful we are to have found Jenna. She is the loveliest, most professional agent in the whole of New York City, and a miracle worker, as far as we are concerned. We have already recommended her to several friends, and will continue to do so in the future. We are so happy in our beautiful home, in our favorite neighborhood, and we know that we have Jenna to thank for all of it!

originalText.text:
What can I say - Jenna made it happen! She set up a website for me overnight with a ton of good options around the area I wanted to explore. Within a few days we had narrowed down the list.

Importantly, she helped me avoid the challenging world of brokers / tack-on fees that so typically characterize the New York apartment hunt. She even managed to negotiate back a few of those (a quick $$$ win).

And of course, it was a good time - in addition to exploring apartments we managed to sneak in a few local spots along the way, helping me truly settle into my new neighborhood.

I'd recommend Jenna to anyone looking for an enjoyable, pain-free New York apartment hunt!

originalText.text: Jenna was our saving grace throughout the entire apartment hunt search. A friend of ours connected us and even with months of headway, Jenna got us familiar with the Compass tools, prepared us for what we needed to provide, gave us an idea of what our budget would allow for and made herself available whenever we had questions. Unfortunately our apartment search landed in the very beginning of unprecedented times with the COVID-19 outbreak in NYC and Jenna navigated everything as if she works in uncharted waters like that daily. We got the apartment we wanted, negotiated a longer lease, locked in a rate, and she was prepared to work with us remotely should anything have fallen through. My husband and I were living in North Carolina during our hunt and working full-time, I could not have managed this move to NYC without Jenna, her expertise and her amazing continuous communication and expectation setting. I will always be recommending everyone I know moving to NYC to her! I even plan to come to Jenna before any future home buying on the east coast :)!

originalText.text: Jenna helped me with my first rental in NYC and it was an absolute pleasure to work with her! Since then she has been my go-to for all broking/real estate needs. She has top-tier market insights and commentary that she provides on a consistent basis. There is no one else I would trust more than Jenna if I need to buy/sell/rent in the city. I refer all my friends to her and there is a reason why!!
